contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} Two ships of the [[United States Navy]] have borne the name '''USS ''Sculpin''''', named in honor of the [[sculpin]]. * The first {{USS|Sculpin|SS-191|3}}, was a [[Sargo class submarine|''Sargo''-class]] [[submarine]], commissioned in 1939 and stricken in 1944. * The second {{USS|Sculpin|SSN-590|3}}, was a [[Skipjack class submarine|''Skipjack''-class]] submarine, commissioned in 1961 and stricken in 1990. {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Sculpin}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
